properties.Title: Special Weather Statement In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: Risk of freezing rain tonight and Saturday morning An approaching frontal system will track across the southern BC interior tonight and Saturday. Flurries are expected tonight and Saturday morning. The warm air aloft combined with near or below zero temperatures at the surface will result in a risk of freezing rain. The flurries with the risk of freezing rain will change to rain showers Saturday afternoon as temperatures rise above zero. Surfaces such as highways, road, walkways and parking lots may become icy and and slippery. Take extra caution when walking or driving in affected areas. ### Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. To report severe weather, send an email to BCstorm@canada.ca or tweet reports using #BCStorm.

properties.Title: Snowfall Warning In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: Snow at times heavy is expected over the Highlands of Inverness and Victoria Counties on Saturday, starting in the morning and persisting into Saturday night. Accumulations of up to 25 centimetres are forecast, with the heaviest amounts expected to fall over the western side of the terrain. Wet snow with lesser accumulations near 5 to 10 centimetres is expected over lower elevations, since temperatures are forecast to remain slightly above freezing. ### Rapidly accumulating snow could make travel difficult over some locations. Visibility may be suddenly reduced at times in heavy snow. Snowfall warnings are issued when significant snowfall is expected. Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. To report severe weather, send an email to NSstorm@canada.ca or tweet reports using #NSStorm.

properties.Title: Update: High Water Advisory Alert Is Being Issued For The Roseau River From Gardenton To Stuartburn
properties.Summary:
Description: Update: This is a Manitoba Emergency Alert. Manitoba Infrastructure's Hydrologic Forecast Centre has issued a High Water Advisory for the Roseau River from Gardenton to Stuartburn due to expected high flows. If you are in the affected area, be watchful of local waterways as flooding is likely to occur. Do not attempt to cross fast flowing waters or waters of unknown depth. Avoid flooded areas. Follow all directions by the local authorities. Listen for updates and take all necessary precautions to stay safe. Up-to-date information is available at www.gov.mb.ca/flooding and www.manitoba511.ca or stay tuned to local media.
Expires: 2019-11-23T11:30:00-06:00
Originated from CAP Alert: Manitoba Emergency Measures Organization, 2019-11-22T11:45:07-06:00, 73D1D33D-C50C-81E6-7C60-3E6661AED930
Area: Roseau River from Gardenton to Stuartburn

properties.Title: Blizzard Warning In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: Blizzard conditions with poor visibility in snow and blowing snow are expected or occurring. Blizzard conditions, with poor visibility in snow and blowing snow, are expected to persist in Ulukhaktok tonight. Conditions will improve throughout the day on Saturday wind speeds begin to ease. ### Travel is expected to be hazardous due to reduced visibility. Blizzard warnings are issued when widespread reduced visibilities of 400 metres or less are expected for at least 6 hours. Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. To report severe weather, send an email to NTstorm@canada.ca or tweet reports using #NTStorm.
